INSERT INTO `craft_entryversions` (`id`, `entryId`, `sectionId`, `creatorId`, `locale`, `notes`, `data`, `dateCreated`, `dateUpdated`, `uid`) VALUES ('23', '32', '7', '1', 'en_us', NULL, '{\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Little Boxes\",\"slug\":\"little-boxes\",\"postDate\":1381718563,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"2\":\"\",\"5\":\"Design Computing\",\"13\":\"\",\"7\":[\"31\"],\"14\":\"<p>Our concept, while still developing is centred around the idea of creating a room in which the user can login to and revisit both their online lives in the present or reverse the room to a time in their past. The goal is to immerse the user in their present and past as seamlessly as possible, while exhibiting their digital lives in an ordinary room, we want to use as many online sources of personal information as we can get, but realise the most ubiquitous source is more than likely Facebook, as it has the largest user base. We want to achieve this with a combination of images, audio, personal information and video, taken directly from Facebook using a mobile to login, with content both from the users profile and content relevant to when the user is choosing to view.<\\/p>\",\"20\":\"\",\"15\":\"\",\"6\":[\"1\"],\"18\":\"\",\"19\":\"<p>Little Boxes is an interactive, digital time-capsule that allows viewers not only to become a part of the piece directly but also to explore digital information in an interesting way. Various wooden boxes of different sizes, shapes and designs are scattered around the space, each with their own screen stored inside. On entering the space, visitors are prompted to do two things; log into their Facebook account and choose a month and year they wish to view.<\\/p>\",\"16\":\"\",\"17\":\"\",\"3\":[\"new:Physical Computing\",\"new:Time Capsules\",\"new:Social Networks\"],\"8\":\"Interaction Design\",\"10\":\"\"}}', '2013-10-14 02:42:43', '2013-10-14 02:42:43', '0acb111c-144d-44bc-9b3d-b8437fb8a93d');
