INSERT INTO `craft_entryversions` (`id`, `entryId`, `sectionId`, `creatorId`, `locale`, `notes`, `data`, `dateCreated`, `dateUpdated`, `uid`) VALUES ('49', '25', '9', '1', 'en_us', NULL, '{\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Interaction Design Assignment Submission\",\"slug\":\"interaction-design-assignment-submission\",\"postDate\":1381662840,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"2\":\"<p><strong>Website Mockups<\\/strong><\\/p><p>Redesigning: <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/animania.net.au\\/2012\\/sydney-september\\\">http:\\/\\/animania.net.au\\/2012\\/sydney-september<\\/a><\\/p><p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.deco2200.net\\/2012\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2012\\/08\\/mockup_site_MAIN.jpg\\\"><img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.deco2200.net\\/2012\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2012\\/08\\/mockup_site_MAIN-1024x814.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" width=\\\"584\\\" height=\\\"464\\\"><\\/a><\\/p><p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.deco2200.net\\/2012\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2012\\/08\\/mockup_site_MAIN_DROPDOWN.jpg\\\"><img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.deco2200.net\\/2012\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2012\\/08\\/mockup_site_MAIN_DROPDOWN-150x150.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" width=\\\"150\\\" height=\\\"150\\\"><\\/a><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.deco2200.net\\/2012\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2012\\/08\\/mockup_site_MAIN_SCROLLEDDOWN.jpg\\\"><img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.deco2200.net\\/2012\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2012\\/08\\/mockup_site_MAIN_SCROLLEDDOWN-150x150.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" width=\\\"150\\\" height=\\\"150\\\"><\\/a><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.deco2200.net\\/2012\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2012\\/08\\/mockup_site_ABOUT.jpg\\\"><img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.deco2200.net\\/2012\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2012\\/08\\/mockup_site_ABOUT-150x150.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" width=\\\"150\\\" height=\\\"150\\\"><\\/a><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.deco2200.net\\/2012\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2012\\/08\\/mockup_site_COSPLAY.jpg\\\"><img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.deco2200.net\\/2012\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2012\\/08\\/mockup_site_COSPLAY-150x150.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" width=\\\"150\\\" height=\\\"150\\\"><\\/a><\\/p><p>The website was designed so that users new to Animania can get a grasp of what the event is all about- through the featured section on the home page(first image), whilst users who know what they are looking for (e.g. competition prizes, etc) can navigate directly to those pages through the easy to use and logical drop-down menus at the top of the site. The home page also includes other important updates underneath the featured box as well the Facebook, Twitter and RSS buttons, and links to the sponsors at the bottom of the page. The red and orange colour scheme is consistent throughout the site and is appropriate for the Anime\\/Cartoony theme and context. We also created some graphics in the top banner to make the site more fun compared to the black and white palette of the current site.<\\/p><p><strong>Smartphone App<\\/strong><\\/p><p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.deco2200.net\\/2012\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2012\\/08\\/mockup_app_MAIN.png\\\"><img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.deco2200.net\\/2012\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2012\\/08\\/mockup_app_MAIN-150x150.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" width=\\\"150\\\" height=\\\"150\\\"><\\/a><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.deco2200.net\\/2012\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2012\\/08\\/mockup_app_NEWS.png\\\"><img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.deco2200.net\\/2012\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2012\\/08\\/mockup_app_NEWS-150x150.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" width=\\\"150\\\" height=\\\"150\\\"><\\/a><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.deco2200.net\\/2012\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2012\\/08\\/mockup_app_PHOTOS.png\\\"><img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.deco2200.net\\/2012\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2012\\/08\\/mockup_app_PHOTOS-150x150.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" width=\\\"150\\\" height=\\\"150\\\"><\\/a><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.deco2200.net\\/2012\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2012\\/08\\/mockup_app_PHOTOS_PRESSEDON.png\\\"><img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.deco2200.net\\/2012\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2012\\/08\\/mockup_app_PHOTOS_PRESSEDON-150x150.png\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" width=\\\"150\\\" height=\\\"150\\\"><\\/a><\\/p><p>The app was designed for practical use at Animania with utility functions such as event information and a map, but also includes the featured function of taking and uploading photos on the spot. The first image is the splash screen you see when first opening the app, it has 4 category buttons with images, which when pressed will take you to the format in the rest of the mockup images- the menu changing into the bar at the top. The news screen shows a list of shortened news feed updates, which when pressed will expand out downwards(image 2). Pressing the Photo section will open up the gallery of photos taken and uploaded by people at the event and pressing on a thumbnail will enlarge the picture as in the last mockup image, with a black opacity background. Finally, the colour scheme of the app was designed to be consistent with the website and the functionality designed with having it simple and compact for quick use on-the-go at the event.<\\/p>\",\"22\":\"\",\"13\":\"\",\"7\":[\"49\"],\"14\":\"\",\"1\":\"Hello\",\"27\":\"Assignment 1\",\"15\":\"\",\"6\":[\"7\",\"1\"],\"18\":\"\",\"16\":\"\",\"17\":\"\",\"24\":\"\",\"25\":\"\",\"3\":\"\",\"10\":\"\"}}', '2013-10-21 06:27:18', '2013-10-21 06:27:18', '36325592-2c66-46d9-9f9c-82338dcdccb3');
INSERT INTO `craft_entryversions` (`id`, `entryId`, `sectionId`, `creatorId`, `locale`, `notes`, `data`, `dateCreated`, `dateUpdated`, `uid`) VALUES ('50', '54', '11', '1', 'en_us', NULL, '{\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Design Lab Research presented at OzChi Conference\",\"slug\":\"design-lab-research-presented-at-ozchi-conference\",\"postDate\":1382325000,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"2\":\"<p>Cutting-edge research in human-computer interaction is the topic of discussion at the annual OzCHI Conference in Melbourne this year.<\\/p><p>OzCHI brings together researchers from across Australia to build networks, find collaborators and stay abreast of the latest knowledge of the way humans interact with computers.<\\/p><p>Design Lab lecturer and program director of the University\'s <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/sydney.edu.au\\/architecture\\/programs_of_study\\/postgraduate\\/IDEA.shtml\\\">Master of Interaction Design and Electronic Arts (IDEA)<\\/a>, Lian Loke, says that OzChi is one of the best ways to present research and gain inspiration from others\' works.<\\/p><p>\\\"The conference does the equivalent of research speed dating. It gets everyone acquainted with everyone else\'s research,\\\" Loke said.<\\/p><p>\\\"We have also been constructing research trees that show the relationships between areas of research. Understanding these degrees of separation between active research projects lets us easily see where the field is headed.\\\"<\\/p><p>Yesterday, Loke and UTS collaborator Professor Toni Robertson ran a workshop, \'The Body in Design\'. The workshop involved designing for bodily experience and understanding bodily engagement in the design process.<\\/p><p><img id=\\\"processed\\\" src=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.arch.usyd.edu.au\\/images\\/news_events\\/2012\\/eloquentrobes.jpg\\\" align=\\\"right\\\" border=\\\"\\\" style=\\\"float: left;\\\" alt=\\\"\\\"><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Design Lab PhD candidate, Ingrid Pohl, will present today a short paper, \'Engaging the sense of touch in interactive architecture\'. The paper explores the ideas manifest in her prototype sensitive surfaces, on display at the Design Lab\'s end of year festival, <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/sydney.edu.au\\/architecture\\/events\\/organisedCacophony.shtml\\\" style=\\\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, Tahoma, sans-serif;\\\">Organised Cacophony<\\/a>.<\\/p><p>IDEA research student, Claudia Nunez-Pacheco has also presented a poster, \'Eloquent Robes\' that explains the work currently exhibited at Organised Cacophony.<\\/p>\",\"22\":\"\",\"13\":\"\",\"7\":[\"53\"],\"14\":\"\",\"1\":\"\\u200bCutting-edge research in human-computer interaction is the topic of discussion at the annual OzCHI Conference in Melbourne this year.\",\"15\":\"\",\"18\":\"\",\"16\":\"\",\"17\":\"\",\"24\":\"\",\"25\":\"\",\"3\":\"\",\"10\":\"\"}}', '2013-10-21 06:41:39', '2013-10-21 06:41:39', '7c294c97-b97b-4466-9c76-4ad8501b7eb9');
